[SN]TITLE[SN]
MPs say UK should take in more Syrian child refugees

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
In the past year millions of people from countries like Syria have made long and dangerous journeys to get to Europe.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
5 January 2016 Last updated at 16:59 GMT
They're often escaping war and poverty in their own country.
Lots of children make the journey, or travel parts of it on their own.
Now, a group of politicians and charities have said that more Syrian children should be helped to come and live in the UK.
Ayshah's gone to a school to find out what kids here think about it.
